I use jit_types_loaded_ to report both the list of types loaded during initialization (through this function) and to report types loaded during runtime (through Jit::NewTypeLoaded). The second use case can't work with passing a ClassLoader* to the compiler as it emits only the debug info for the newly loaded types.

If we want to move this code to the compiler (to jit_types_loaded) then we either have to add a new method for it and have 2 method to pass type information over to the jit or make the interface of jit_types_loaded_ more complicated with either accepting a mirror::Class* or accepting a ClassLoader*. I don't think any of this option is better then the current one with implementing it in the runtime but let me know if you have different preferences.

